race.comment: Cranbourne Cup time. It's hard to go past SABAJ (15) off the big win at Flemington last start, settling back on heavy ground but charging away off a strong speed to win with authority. He's a progressive 4yo who started $4.80 in the G3 Silver Eagle behind Linebacker for the new stable when fresh. The only niggle here is how big a start he gives them from the draw. ENXUTO (14) might have worn thin with a few punters. He was unlucky in a couple of runs at Flemington over 1400m, then seemingly had every chance to 1600m on the 5 day turnaround last time when well backed behind Apulia. We're getting an each way price about him now from a soft draw, he can bounce back. WARNIE (1) was a strong winner in G2 company last start, given a great ride there. 1600m will be fine and he's not poorly in even with top weight. AIR ASSAULT (3) is flying in Adelaide and will be up on speed, respecting. STEPARTY (2) was very good behind WARNIE two back, wipe last time and he's right in this.
